{"title":"Velo Orange Next Generation Crazy Bars go wider w/40mm rise for better handling","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/02/08/velo-orange-next-generation-crazy-bars-go-wider-w-40mm-rise-for-better-handling/","date":1612813082000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p><span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-box-3\"></span>Eight years on from their inaugural ride, Velo Orange’s Crazy Bars have been refreshed, now wider, with more rise, less backsweep and shorter horns. The unusual 3-piece aluminium bars have long been a popular choice in the bikepacking and touring communities, thanks to their generous sweep, compatibility with bikepacking bags and, undoubtedly, their made-you-look vibes. Let’s dig deeper into the next generation Crazy Bars.</p><figure id=\"attachment_251139\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-251139\"><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-crazy-bars-next-generation-touring-handlebars-780mm-wide-40mm-rise-35-degree-backsweep.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-crazy-bars-next-generation-touring-handlebars-780mm-wide-40mm-rise-35-degree-backsweep.jpg\" alt=\"velo orange next generation crazy bars touring bikepacking 780mm wide 40mm riser\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-crazy-bars-next-generation-touring-handlebars-780mm-wide-40mm-rise-35-degree-backsweep.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-crazy-bars-next-generation-touring-handlebars-780mm-wide-40mm-rise-35-degree-backsweep.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/vel