ttps://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-crazy-bars-next-generation-touring-handlebars-780mm-wide-40mm-rise-35-degree-backsweep-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-crazy-bars-next-generation-touring-handlebars-780mm-wide-40mm-rise-35-degree-backsweep-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-crazy-bars-next-generation-touring-handlebars-780mm-wide-40mm-rise-35-degree-backsweep-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-crazy-bars-next-generation-touring-handlebars-780mm-wide-40mm-rise-35-degree-backsweep-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-crazy-bars-next-generation-touring-handlebars-780mm-wide-40mm-rise-35-degree-backsweep-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-251139\">The main bar uses a 22.2mm grip area so MTB grips, levers, and shifters are compatible</figcaption></figure><p>The Velo Orange Crazy Bars have seen a number of changes over the years; materials used, tubing shapes, finish and clamp area size have all seen tweaks. It has also been the inspiration of another bar in the Velo Orange line-up; the Seine Bar is essentially the Crazy Bar minus the forward horns.</p><figure id=\"attachment_251140\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-251140\"><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-bikepacking-handlebars-next-generation-crazy-bars-touring-40mm-rise.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-bikepacking-handlebars-next-generation-crazy-bars-touring-40mm-rise.jpg\" alt=\"purple velo orange with next genera