ploads/2021/02/velo-orange-bikepacking-handlebars-next-generation-crazy-bars-touring-40mm-rise.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-bikepacking-handlebars-next-generation-crazy-bars-touring-40mm-rise-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-bikepacking-handlebars-next-generation-crazy-bars-touring-40mm-rise-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-bikepacking-handlebars-next-generation-crazy-bars-touring-40mm-rise-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-bikepacking-handlebars-next-generation-crazy-bars-touring-40mm-rise-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-bikepacking-handlebars-next-generation-crazy-bars-touring-40mm-rise-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-bikepacking-handlebars-next-generation-crazy-bars-touring-40mm-rise-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-bikepacking-handlebars-next-generation-crazy-bars-touring-40mm-rise-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-251140\">The bar has a 31.8mm diameter stem clamp area</figcaption></figure><p>So, what’s new this time? The next generation Crazy bars are now 780mm wide, with the sweep reduced to 35°. Velo Orange say those numbers deliver the perfect balance of leverage for out of the saddle climbs and natural wrist positioning for regular riding. The extra width adds real estate to the cockpit, allowing riders to spec longer grips, with more brake/shifter compatibility and space for mounting lights or a cycle computer.</p><figure id=\"attachment_251138\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-251138\"><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-next-generation-crazy-bars-horns-touring-bikepacking-handlebars.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-next-generation-crazy-bars-horns-touring-bikepacking-handlebars.jpg\" alt=\"velo orange next generation crazy bars for bikepacking touring setups\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-next-generation-crazy-bars-horns-touring-bikepacking-handlebars.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-next-generation-crazy-bars-horns-touring-bikepacking-handlebars.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-next-generation-crazy-bars-horns-touring-bikepacking-handlebars-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-next-generation-crazy-bars-horns-touring-bikepacking-handlebars-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-next-generation-crazy-bars-horns-touring-bikepacking-handlebars-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-next-generation-crazy-bars-horns-touring-bikepacking-handlebars-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-next-generation-crazy-bars-horns-touring-bikepacking-handlebars-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-next-generation-crazy-bars-horns-touring-bikepacking-handlebars-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-next-generation-crazy-bars-horns-touring-bikepacking-handlebars-630x420.jpg 630w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-next-generation-crazy-bars-horns-touring-bikepacking-handlebars.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-next-generation-crazy-bars-horns-touring-bikepacking-handlebars-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-next-generation-crazy-bars-horns-touring-bikepacking-handlebars-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-next-generation-crazy-bars-horns-touring-bikepacking-handlebars-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-next-generation-crazy-bars-horns-touring-bikepacking-handlebars-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-next-generation-crazy-bars-horns-touring-bikepacking-handlebars-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-next-generation-crazy-bars-horns-touring-bikepacking-handlebars-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-next-generation-crazy-bars-horns-touring-bikepacking-handlebars-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-251138\">The horns have an outside clamp diameter of 23.8mm, so inverse brake levers and bar-end shifters are compatible</figcaption></figure><p>Now for the Crazy bit… the horns. After all, the bar wouldn’t be much to look at without the addition of the TT esque hand position option. These have been shortened to 110mm, but still retain the ability to mount bar end shifters.</p><p>Velo Orange say this allows significantly easier access to all of the positions without having to reach to the extremes of the bars. They sit 420mm apart from one another.<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-medrectangle-3\"></span></p><figure id=\"attachment_251141\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-251141\"><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-crazy-bars-next-gen.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-crazy-bars-next-gen.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-crazy-bars-next-gen.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-crazy-bars-next-gen.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-crazy-bars-next-gen-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-crazy-bars-next-gen-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-crazy-bars-next-gen-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-crazy-bars-next-gen-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/velo-orange-crazy-bars-next-gen-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpen